# Current Architecture (Implemented — 2026-03-14)

**Region:** us-east-1 (N. Virginia)
**Cost:** ~$24-25/month (unchanged from in-place deploy)

## Architecture Overview

```
Internet
   |
CloudFront (E249N2JVWYGK8A)
   |
   ├── /graphql → EIP (18.206.134.231) → EC2 (CI/CD-managed) [Public Subnet, port 8080]
   │                                        |
   │                                     RDS (hestia-dev-db) [Private Subnet]
   │
   └── /* → S3 (hestia-dev-frontend) [Static SPA]
```

## Blue-Green Deploy Flow

```
CI/CD (GitHub Actions)
  │
  ├─ 1. Build & push Docker image to ECR (unchanged)
  │
  ├─ 2. Launch NEW EC2 from Launch Template (lt-0fc2e9d34dcaf6006)
  │
  ├─ 3. Wait for instance ready + SSM agent registration (~60-90s)
  │
  ├─ 4. Run deploy.sh ON new instance via SSM
  │      (ECR pull, SSM config fetch, docker run)
  │
  ├─ 5. Health check new instance (curl :8080/actuator/health)
  │
  ├─ 6. Swap Elastic IP: old instance → new instance
  │      (single API call with --allow-reassociation, ~0-5s blip)
  │
  ├─ 7. Verify health via Elastic IP
  │
  └─ 8. Terminate old instance
```

**Rollback is automatic:**
- If health check fails at step 5 → terminate new instance, old untouched
- If post-swap check fails at step 7 → re-associate EIP to old, terminate new

## Instance Tagging Convention

| Tag | Value | Purpose |
|-----|-------|---------|
| `Status` | `active` | Currently serving traffic via EIP |
| `Status` | `provisioning` | Being set up by blue-green script |
| `Status` | `draining` | Old instance, about to be terminated |
| `ManagedBy` | `ci-cd` | Launched by GitHub Actions (not Terraform) |
| `DeployedAt` | ISO 8601 timestamp | When the instance was deployed |
| `ImageTag` | Docker image tag | Which version is running |

## Key Resources (Dev)

| Resource | ID/Value |
|----------|----------|
| Elastic IP | `eipalloc-02f586bc05fd635bc` (18.206.134.231) |
| EIP DNS | `ec2-18-206-134-231.compute-1.amazonaws.com` |
| Launch Template | `lt-0fc2e9d34dcaf6006` |
| Public Subnet | `aws_subnet.public[0]` |
| CloudFront Dist | `E249N2JVWYGK8A` |
| Frontend URL | `https://d1twtjfgg5e272.cloudfront.net` |

## Downtime During Deploy

- **Old (in-place):** 10-30s (container stop/start gap) + dirty-state failures
- **Blue-green:** 0-5s (EIP reassociation propagation). CloudFront may retry 1-2 failed requests.

