# IAM Permissions for Blue-Green Deploy

The `github-actions` role (`terraform/cicd/main.tf`) needs these additional permissions for blue-green:

| Permission | Resource | Purpose |
|------------|----------|---------|
| `ec2:RunInstances` | Launch Template ARN | Launch new instances |
| `ec2:DescribeInstances` | `*` | Find current active instance |
| `ec2:DescribeInstanceStatus` | `*` | Wait for instance ready |
| `ec2:TerminateInstances` | `hestia-*` tagged instances | Cleanup old instance |
| `ec2:CreateTags` | `*` | Tag instances with Status |
| `ec2:AssociateAddress` | EIP ARN | Swap EIP to new instance |
| `ec2:DisassociateAddress` | `*` | Remove EIP from old instance |
| `ec2:DescribeAddresses` | `*` | Find EIP details |
| `iam:PassRole` | EC2 role ARN | Pass role to new instance |
| `ssm:SendCommand` | `*` | Run deploy.sh on new instance |
| `ssm:GetCommandInvocation` | `*` | Check deploy.sh result |
| `ssm:DescribeInstanceInformation` | `*` | Verify SSM agent ready |

## IAM Gotchas

- `ssm:DescribeParameters` requires `Resource: "*"` — cannot scope to specific paths
- `iam:PassRole` must target the specific EC2 role ARN
- `ec2:RunInstances` needs access to the Launch Template, AMI, subnet, security group, and instance profile

